<Link id="l00538" /><CodeLine lineNumber="538"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00539" /><CodeLine lineNumber="539"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Considering forming a binary search, we should find the number of nodes</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00540" /><CodeLine lineNumber="540"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// which is same as the number of comparisons when lowered. For a given</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00541" /><CodeLine lineNumber="541"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// number of clusters, n, we can define a recursive function, f(n), to find</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00542" /><CodeLine lineNumber="542"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the number of nodes in the tree. The recursion is :</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="543"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// f(n) = 1 + f(n/2) + f (n - n/2), when n &gt; 3,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="544"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// and f(n) = n, when n &lt;= 3</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="545"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This will lead a binary tree where the leaf should be either f(2) or f(3)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="546"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// when n &gt; 3  So, the number of comparisons from leaves should be n, while</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="547"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the number of non-leaf should be :</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="548"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   2^(log2(n) - 1) - 1</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="549"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   = 2^log2(n) &#42; 2^-1 - 1</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="550"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   = n / 2 - 1</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="551"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Considering comparisons from leaf and non-leaf nodes, we can estimate the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="552"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// number of comparisons in a simple closed form :</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="553"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   n + n / 2 - 1 = n &#42; 3 / 2 - 1</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="554" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-inlinecost-cpp-/#a374e842507732fae7dbbd03f9a137759"><Highlight kind="normal">int64&#95;t <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-inlinecost-cpp-/#a374e842507732fae7dbbd03f9a137759">getExpectedNumberOfCompare</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> NumCaseCluster) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="555"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> 3 &#42; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static&#95;cast&lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">int64&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">&gt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(NumCaseCluster) / 2 - 1;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="556"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Inlining cost measured in abstract units, accounts for all the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instructions expected to be executed for a given function invocation.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02910" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2910"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Test that there are no attribute conflicts between Caller and Callee</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02911" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2911"><Highlight kind="comment">///        that prevent inlining.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02912" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2912" lineLink="#ad6e6415d4d2e809c620d08fb23c1544f"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="#ad6e6415d4d2e809c620d08fb23c1544f">functionsHaveCompatibleAttributes</a>(</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2913"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &#42;Caller, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &#42;Callee, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targettransforminfo">TargetTransformInfo</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#aa0d69e81725c10fa5407f0bf34462068">TTI</a>,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02914" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2914"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function-ref">function&#95;ref</a>&lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetlibraryinfo">TargetLibraryInfo</a> &amp;(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &amp;)&gt; &amp;GetTLI) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2915"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Note that CalleeTLI must be a copy not a reference. The legacy pass manager</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2916"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// caches the most recently created TLI in the TargetLibraryInfoWrapperPass</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02917" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2917"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// object, and always returns the same object (which is overwritten on each</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02918" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2918"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// GetTLI call). Therefore we copy the first result.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02919" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2919"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> CalleeTLI = GetTLI(&#42;Callee);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02920" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2920"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="#a94cba06a633881068835d763f3ae3dee">IgnoreTTIInlineCompatible</a> ||</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02921" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2921"><Highlight kind="normal">          <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#aa0d69e81725c10fa5407f0bf34462068">TTI</a>.areInlineCompatible(Caller, Callee)) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02922" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2922"><Highlight kind="normal">         GetTLI(&#42;Caller).areInlineCompatible(CalleeTLI,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02923" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2923"><Highlight kind="normal">                                             <a href="#a57032bf75155bd7c0b9e53e9f0c96f04">InlineCallerSupersetNoBuiltin</a>) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02924" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2924"><Highlight kind="normal">         AttributeFuncs::areInlineCompatible(&#42;Caller, &#42;Callee);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02925" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2925"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02926" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2926"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02927" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2927" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abac7688a1d6c52dc96e04dd56827df60"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abac7688a1d6c52dc96e04dd56827df60">llvm::getCallsiteCost</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targettransforminfo">TargetTransformInfo</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#aa0d69e81725c10fa5407f0bf34462068">TTI</a>, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callbase">CallBase</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#ga9c9cf6ad55eb23d77d083a184e416c09">Call</a>,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2928"><Highlight kind="normal">                          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/datalayout">DataLayout</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/arm/armslshardening-cpp/#ad467c4ab9119043f9b7750ab986be61a">DL</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02929" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2929"><Highlight kind="normal">  int64&#95;t <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a19921a3ceb99548f498d3df118eda9ed">Cost</a> = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02930" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2930"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a> = 0, E = <a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#ga9c9cf6ad55eb23d77d083a184e416c09">Call</a>.arg&#95;size(); <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a> != E; ++<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02931" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2931"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#ga9c9cf6ad55eb23d77d083a184e416c09">Call</a>.isByValArgument(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>)) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02932" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2932"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We approximate the number of loads and stores needed by dividing the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02933" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2933"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// size of the byval type by the target&#39;s pointer size.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02934" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2934"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pointertype">PointerType</a> &#42;PTy = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ac4fc845f5ed92de63cd4474f128f5fc5">cast&lt;PointerType&gt;</a>(<a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#ga9c9cf6ad55eb23d77d083a184e416c09">Call</a>.getArgOperand(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>)-&gt;getType());</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02935" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2935"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/typesize">TypeSize</a> = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/arm/armslshardening-cpp/#ad467c4ab9119043f9b7750ab986be61a">DL</a>.getTypeSizeInBits(<a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#ga9c9cf6ad55eb23d77d083a184e416c09">Call</a>.getParamByValType(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02936" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2936"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> AS = PTy-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pointertype/#af8aeced5e71d2589fa3e9791043af5cb">getAddressSpace</a>();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02937" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2937"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> PointerSize = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/arm/armslshardening-cpp/#ad467c4ab9119043f9b7750ab986be61a">DL</a>.getPointerSizeInBits(AS);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02938" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2938"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Ceiling division.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02939" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2939"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> NumStores = (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/typesize">TypeSize</a> + PointerSize - 1) / PointerSize;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02940" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2940"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02941" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2941"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If it generates more than 8 stores it is likely to be expanded as an</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02942" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2942"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// inline memcpy so we take that as an upper bound. Otherwise we assume</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2943"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// one load and one store per word copied.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02944" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2944"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// FIXME: The maxStoresPerMemcpy setting from the target should be used</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2945"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// here instead of a magic number of 8, but it&#39;s not available via</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2946"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// DataLayout.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2947"><Highlight kind="normal">      NumStores = std::min(NumStores, 8U);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2948"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02949" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2949"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a19921a3ceb99548f498d3df118eda9ed">Cost</a> += 2 &#42; NumStores &#42; <a href="#abd4fe6436780bc5172e1f00bd5c3ceaf">InstrCost</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02950" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2950"><Highlight kind="normal">    &#125; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02951" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2951"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For non-byval arguments subtract off one instruction per call</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02952" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2952"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// argument.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02953" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2953"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a19921a3ceb99548f498d3df118eda9ed">Cost</a> += <a href="#abd4fe6436780bc5172e1f00bd5c3ceaf">InstrCost</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02954" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2954"><Highlight kind="normal">    &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02955" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2955"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02956" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2956"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The call instruction also disappears after inlining.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02957" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2957"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a19921a3ceb99548f498d3df118eda9ed">Cost</a> += <a href="#abd4fe6436780bc5172e1f00bd5c3ceaf">InstrCost</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
